==English==


===Pronunciation===
*\Bott"ler`\


===Adjective===

#(Australia and New Zealand) '''[[Slang]]''' for: Brilliant. Excellent!. Exceptionally Good. Extraordinary. Fantastic. Great. Remarkable.  Splendid. Super. Wonderful. Remarkable. Awesome. Well executed. 
#Of good repute. 
#According to the Urban Slang Dictionary, a bottler is something that is so good that it is worth bottling up and keeping.

===Noun===

#Entities or manufacturers that produce beverages and place them in bottles, usually in bulk quantitites.
#(Wikipedia) Trucks that specialize in transporting [[bottle]]d goods in crates.
#(Wikipedia) An [[IRC]] client (or a [[plugin]] for an IRC client) that scans text sent from IRC. It offer bots such as [[XDCC]] bots and also queries bots for file lists. It then lets the user download files without having to look for them themselves.
#(British Slang): A coward.
#Colloquial: A drunk.

